headline: New Research from the Humana Foundation Examines Food Insecurity Crisis Among Kentucky Seniors
summary: LOUISVILLE, Ky., November 19, 2025--The Humana Foundation, the philanthropic arm of Humana Inc. for the past 44 years, today announced the publication of its new issue brief, Senior Food Insecurity in Kentucky: A Growing Public Health Challenge. The brief examines the complex web of challenges the state’s older adults face in accessing nutritious foods and offers a call to action with recommended investments that can help overcome those barriers.

headline: What Humana (HUM)'s Profit Drop and Lowered Outlook Mean For Shareholders
summary: In early November 2025, Humana Inc. reported third quarter results showing increased revenue to US$32.65 billion, but net income dropped to US$195 million compared to the previous year. The company also completed a US$200 million share buyback and revised its 2025 annual earnings guidance downward to approximately US$12.26 per share.
